Surgical resection of cystic intraductal papillary adenocarcinoma of the bile duct: report of a case. We describe a cystic intraductal papillary neoplasm of bile duct (IPNB) of adenocarcinoma treated with surgical resection. An 82-year-old man was admitted to our hospital because of distension of the right upper quadrant of the abdomen. On admission, a huge nontender mass was palpated in the right upper abdomen. Initial laboratory tests revealed the following serum values: aspartate aminotransferase, 123 IU/L alanine aminotransferase, 113 IU/L